<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Open Lower  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were lower in Monday's early
trading.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average was down 20 points in the early
going. Losing issues on the New York Stock Exchange held a 8-to-5
lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index was off 56 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index was down nine points.
</P>
<P>
   The popular Wall Street averages are giving back some of their
Friday gains.
</P>
<P>
   The market also is facing some early weakness after declines in
overseas trading.
</P>
<P>
   Tokyo's Nikkei fell 1.3 percent in the first day of trading
since last Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices were edging higher.
</P>
<P>
   There are no economic reports of any significance due until
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Nevertheless, the thought of higher interest rates remains with
the market, following Friday's stronger-than-expected report on
unemployment.
</P>
