<HEADLINE> Man killed while sitting in road, alcohol involved  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   PARISH, N.Y. (AP) -- A 27-year-old man was sitting in the middle
of a county road when he was struck and killed by a car, state
police said today.
</P>
<P>
   Jeffrey L. Hirsch of Parish was struck about 2:30 a.m. Sunday on
county Route 26 by a car driven by Frank J. Sobotka, 37, also of
Parish, troopers said.
</P>
<P>
   Sobotka spotted Hirsch when he crested a hill near an
intersection about 35 miles north of Syracuse, but could not avoid
him in time, said state police Sgt. Dale Crisp.
</P>
<P>
   Sobotka was charged with driving while intoxicated and released
on his own recognizance. Hirsch, too, had been drinking before the
accident, according to friends who said he apparently was trying to
walk home.
</P>
</TEXT>
