<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Down 65; Dow Down 5  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mostly lower at the start of trading
today as investors worried about rising interest rates and took
some profits from Friday's market rally.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was down 5.22 at 10,572.64.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also lower. The Nasdaq composite
index was down 65.02 at 3,751.80 and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index was down 8.51 to 1,424.12.
</P>
<P>
   Traders said many investors were selling stocks to capture
short-term gains from a solid rally on Friday, when the Dow rose
165 points and the Nasdaq rose 96 points. With interest rate
worries settling over Wall Street, many investors appeared
reluctant to take significant new positions. Trading was extremely
light.
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Reserve is expected to raise interest rates by as
much as a half-percentage point at its next meeting on May 16. The
Fed has raised interest rates five times since last June in a
series of modest, quarter-percentage point hikes.
</P>
<P>
   Rising interest rates are generally bad for stocks because they
cut into corporate profits by increasing the cost of borrowing
money. This time around, however, many analysts believe a heftier
increase could mollify investors because it might signify that the
Fed is nearing the end of its cycle of rate increases.
</P>
<P>
   Technology stocks, which led Friday's rally, were mostly lower
today. Hewlett-Packard fell 3[ to 133| and Intel fell 3 to 120].
</P>
<P>
   Sun Microsystems fell 3 3/16 to 87 5/16 and PMC-Sierra fell 5}
to 174\.
</P>
<P>
   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 4-to-3 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 102.08 million
shares, behind Friday's quiet pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 3.83 to 509.01.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average fell 1.3 percent. In
afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was down 1.5 percent,
Britain's FT-SE 100 was down 0.7 percent, and France's CAC-40 was
down 0.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
