<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Monday, May 8, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   'Love Bug' Virus Suspect Arrested
</P>
<P>
   MANILA, Philippines (AP) -- Philippine police today arrested a
bank employee who along with his girlfriend is suspected of links
to the ''ILOVEYOU'' computer virus that has overwhelmed networks
around the world. But relatives of the man, Reomel Ramones, said
they believe the real culprit may be a third person who lived in
the couple's apartment -- the girlfriend's unemployed sister, who
recently graduated from a computer school that a U.S. security firm
has been tied to the ''Love Bug'' virus. Investigators raided the
apartment in Pandacan, a lower-middle-class Manila neighborhood,
and seized computer diskettes, wires, telephones and other computer
accessories, officials said. Two FBI agents accompanied the
investigators in the apartment raid, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Microsoft Prepares Counterproposal
</P>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Microsoft Corp. is reported to be exploring a
number of possible alternatives to the government's plan for a
company breakup. The company is due to submit its response to the
government on Wednesday. Spokesman Mark Murray said today it is too
soon to talk publicly about what Microsoft will do. But media
reports suggest it will raise the possibility of allowing computer
makers more flexibility in installing and altering the Windows
operating system. Another possibility is that Microsoft also might
suggest offering a version of Windows without the Internet Explorer
Web browser tied to it. The linkage was one of the first charges
leveled at the company by the U.S. Justice Department and 19 state
attorneys general.
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Sheds 122; Dow Off 14
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mostly lower today, with technology
stocks leading the decline. But financial stocks shook off growing
interest-rate worries and helped the Dow contain its losses. Many
analysts believe a heftier rate hike by the Federal Reserve next
week could mollify investors because it might signify that the Fed
is finally nearing the end of its cycle of rate increases. Just
before 3 p.m. EDT, the Dow industrials 14.36 at 10,563.50. On the
NYSE, decliners led advancers 1,737-1,162. The Nasdaq was 122.67 at
3,694.15.
</P>
