<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-08 15:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Michael J. Fox Feels Parkinson Woes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RADNOR, Pa. (AP) -- Michael J. Fox says he's beginning to feel
the effects of Parkinson's disease.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm slower than I was. I'm not as dexterous. I'm as strong as
I was, but not as agile,'' he said in TV Guide's latest issue.
</P>
<P>
   Still, Fox, 38, who was diagnosed with the debilitating muscle
disease seven years ago, said he is optimistic that a cure will be
found.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm completely confident that in my 50s this will be gone,''
he said.
</P>
<P>
   He said he has grown up a lot since he first learned he had the
disease.
</P>
<P>
   ''Not to get too mawkish about it, but I didn't become a man
until I had this,'' he said. ''And it has given me kind of a
serenity and a clarity that I wouldn't have had otherwise.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
