<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Elton John Sees the Big Picture  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- It's a fitting tribute to the self-proclaimed
''god of shopping.''
</P>
<P>
   Elton John stood outside Selfridges department store in London
on Monday to see a huge picture of himself go up above the
entrance.
</P>
<P>
   The singer's image will form part of what is being billed as the
world's largest photograph, stretching about 900 feet around the
building.
</P>
<P>
   The work, which is 60 feet high, was dreamed up by artist Sam
Taylor-Wood, who said she wanted to create a modern-day version of
an Elgin Marble frieze, using images of cultural icons instead of
Greek gods.
</P>
<P>
   John is pictured sitting down and staring onto the street,
surrounded by the British actors Ray Winstone, Timothy Spall,
Richard E. Grant, Adrian Dunbar and Jane Horrocks.
</P>
<P>
   The photograph will remain wrapped around the store until
October.
</P>
</TEXT>
