<HEADLINE> AP Board, Management Officers Pick  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Donald E. Newhouse, president of Advance
Publications Inc. and of The Star-Ledger of Newark, N.J., was
re-elected chairman of the board of directors of The Associated
Press on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   David E. Easterly, president and COO of Cox Enterprises Inc.,
representing the Dayton (Ohio) Daily News, was elected vice
chairman.
</P>
<P>
   Louis D. Boccardi was re-elected president and chief executive
officer of the news cooperative.
</P>
<P>
   Other AP management officers re-elected to one-year terms were
Patrick T. O'Brien, senior vice president and chief financial
officer; James M. Donna, vice president and secretary; and vice
presidents Vincent J. Alabiso, Claude E. Erbsen, Walter R. Mears,
John W. Reid, Thomas E. Slaughter, Wick Temple and James R.
Williams.
</P>
<P>
   Jonathan P. Wolman, executive editor, also was elected vice
president.
</P>
<P>
   Daniel M. Boruch was re-elected treasurer, and Salvatore Focella
and Ann Randolph were re-elected assistant treasurers. Other AP
management officers re-elected were assistant secretaries Lilo
Jedelhauser and Greg Groce.
</P>
