   Salon.com Buys Audio Distributor
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Moving from the printed word to the spoken word,
Internet magazine Salon is buying MP3Lit.com, a site offering
readings and lectures from authors in MP3, a digital format used
for audio files. The $5 million deal announced today gives Salon a
head start in offering audio on its main site as well as another
way of promoting its writers and columnists on other sites. Unlike
competitor Audible.com, which sells audio file downloads,
MP3Lit.com gives away its files a practice that will continue at
Salon as a way to draw in advertising revenues and promote book
sales.
