$570 million deal that company officials say will form the world's
largest polymer services company. The combination links Geon's
manufacturing strengths with Hanna's experience in making and
distributing polymer products, which can be plastics, rubber,
resins and industrial film. Geon's specialty is vinyl plastics.
When combined, the companies expect to benefit from raw materials
savings, market-related opportunities and overhead reductions by
2002.
</P>
