<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-08 21:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Fall; Dollar Up Vs Yen  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stocks fell early Tuesday following a retreat
in technology shares on Wall Street. The dollar was higher against
the yen.
</P>
<P>
   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average shed 224.49 points,
or 1.23 percent, to 17,975.47 in the first one hour of trading. On
Monday, the average closed down 239.40 points, or 1.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar bought 109.22 yen, up 0.40 yen from late Monday in
Tokyo and also above its late New York level of 109.03 yen.
</P>
<P>
   On the stock market, leading high-tech and information
technology-related shares were among early losers in line with a
plunge in the U.S. Nasdaq composite index, which fell 147.44 points
to close at 3,669.38 Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Also in New York, the Dow Jones industrial average gained 25.77
points to 10,603.63 at Monday's close.
</P>
<P>
   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the
first section was down 21.29 points, or 1.25 percent, to 1,675.23.
The TOPIX closed down 6.06 points, or 0.35 percent, the day before.
</P>
<P>
   In currency dealings, traders said the dollar moved higher on
buying mainly from U.S. banks.
</P>
<P>
   The greenback has been in demand in recent days against the yen
amid expectations the Federal Reserve may raise interest rates to
head off inflationary pressure in the United States. The Fed's
policy board meeting is scheduled for May 16.
</P>
<P>
   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 97.74 yen, down from
97.92 yen late Monday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond fell
to 1.7250 percent from Monday's finish of 1.7350 percent. Its price
rose 0.09 point to 100.64.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: Tokyo Stock Exchange: http://www.tse.or.jp./
</P>
</TEXT>
