<HEADLINE> Brewers Manager Tossed From Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Milwaukee Brewers manager Davey Lopes was ejected
from Monday night's game against the Chicago Cubs in the fifth
inning for arguing a called strike.
</P>
<P>
   It was the rookie manager's first ejection.
</P>
<P>
   Jose Hernandez took a 1-1 pitch that plate umpire Chuck
Meriwether called a strike, and Lopes immediately charged out of
the dugout.
</P>
<P>
   Lopes and Meriwether argued for about three minutes.
</P>
